column1: The Lexington Traffic Management Center will be closed on Monday January 15 in observance of Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. Day.
Regular traffic reports will resume Tuesday January 16 at 6:30 a.m.

column3: Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. Freedom March:
column4: Monday January 15 from 10 a.m. to 11 a.m. in downtown Lexington.

column3: Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. Freedom March:
column4: Rolling street closures starting from Heritage Hall proceeding on Vine St to Rose St to Main St, and back to Heritage Hall.
